column1: NGR is the sewage works at Lunt. The gauge moved 300yds west in 1908 and 400 yards N in 1909; the main sewer at Lunt was built in 1908. The 1950s records have the gauge at S0963958, 0.5 miles South; MIDAS has it in a similar position 0.5 miles SSE. The relationships to the church and station in the early records are more consistent with the NGR that is proposed. Could be +/- 800m
1945 and 1946 have some amended results with no explanation. Results left in this record
